name: Maximizer
description: Add a Maximizer CRM  Instance to connect your existing Maximizer account to the MaximizerCRM Hub, allowing you to manage addressbookentries, companies, contacts, addresses, and opportunities,etc. across multiple Maximizer Elements. You will need your Maximizer CRM account information to add an instance.

The configuration is defined via JSON, an example of which is as follows - { "contacts": { "url": "/hubs/helpdesk/contacts", “idField”: “user.id”, “datesConfiguration”: { "updatedDateField": "user.updated_at", "updatedDateFormat": "yyyy-MM-dd'T'HH:mm:ssX", “createdDateField”: “user.created_at”, “createdDateFormat": "yyyy-MM-dd'T'HH:mm:ssX" }, "pageSize": 10000 } }

parameters.name: where
parameters.description: The CEQL search expression. The operators available are "=", "!=", ">", ">=", "<", "<=", "LIKE", "IS", "AND" and "OR". An example of a single where query would be CompanyName = 'CloudElements' . An example of a multiple where query would be firstName = 'Brian' AND LastName LIKE 'C%' . The fields that supports filtering are [ Type, Email, MrMs, FirstName, LastName, MiddleName, CompanyName, Department, Division, CreationDate, LastModifyDate ]
